{"type":"message","id":"0797b4d0","parentId":"acf95b0f","timestamp":"2026-04-11T14:02:17.064Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_ngezbd4cad3t7g0n5oi7iqzi","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"    if time_str == current_time:\n        last_run_val = last_run.get(job_name, \"\")\n        if not last_run_val.startswith(current_date):\n            return True\n        if last_run_val != f\"{current_date}-{current_time}\":\n            return True\n\n    # Minute list: \"00,15,30,45\"\n    if \",\" in time_str:\n        allowed_minutes = [int(m) for m in time_str.split(\",\")]\n        if minute in allowed_minutes:\n            last_run_val = last_run.get(job_name, \"\")\n            if not last_run_val.startswith(current_date):\n                return True\n\n    return False\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    state = load_state()\n    now = get_ist_time()\n    current_date = now.strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d\")\n\n    for time_str, job_name in SCHEDULE:\n        if should_run(time_str, now, state[\"last_run\"], job_name):\n            run_job(job_name)\n\n            # Send completion notification - ALWAYS send, manual or cron\n            log_done = f\"[{now.strftime('%H:%M IST')}] ✅ Completed job: {job_name}\"\n            try:\n                subprocess.run(\n                    [\n                        \"openclaw\",\n                        \"message\",\n                        \"send\",\n\n[17 more lines in file. Use offset=265 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775916137034}}
{"type":"message","id":"c6e177c1","parentId":"0797b4d0","timestamp":"2026-04-11T14:02:29.529Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"✅ **Root Cause Found:**\n\nThe bug is in the `should_run()` logic for the 15min interval jobs.\n\n**BUG:**\nFor `00,15,30,45` jobs, the scheduler checks `if not last_run_val.startswith(current_date)` - it will only run ONCE per day per interval time, not once every 15 minutes. It never resets the flag after that first run, so it will never run again for the rest of the day.\n\nThat's why you didn't see any notifications. The job ran once at 16:15, marked itself as run for today, and will not run again until tomorrow.\n\nThis is the critical bug. Fixing it now."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"bytedance-seed/dola-seed-2.0-pro:free","usage":{"input":31853,"output":158,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32011,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775916137065,"responseId":"021775916137957a262ecc6d4c5ad12813924c87f6f247fc2b11e"}}
