{"type":"message","id":"9a73a397","parentId":"68f11154","timestamp":"2026-04-11T15:17:19.181Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"✅ Fixed. Here is the corrected logic:\n\n```python\n    # Minute list: \"00,15,30,45\"\n    if \",\" in time_str:\n        allowed_minutes = [int(m) for m in time_str.split(\",\")]\n        if minute in allowed_minutes:\n            last_run_val = last_run.get(job_name, \"\")\n            expected_run_key = f\"{current_date}-{now.strftime('%H:%M')}\"\n            if last_run_val != expected_run_key:\n                return True\n```\n\nThe bug was it only checked date, not the actual time. Now every single 15min slot is tracked individually. Jobs will run correctly every 15 minutes now."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"bytedance-seed/dola-seed-2.0-pro:free","usage":{"input":32500,"output":158,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32658,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775920628215,"responseId":"021775920629401798132a7c84228b35f5c1a465b83379e6dcd33"}}
