{"type":"message","id":"a71a2818","parentId":"ffef4703","timestamp":"2026-04-11T15:32:55.503Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"✅ **FULL ROOT CAUSE ANALYSIS:**\n\nFound it. This is an off-by-one bug.\n\n**The bug:**\nThe git-auto-commit job is configured for `01` minute (every hour at :01). But in `should_run()` there is **ZERO handling for single minute jobs**. There are only handlers for `HH:MM` exact times, and comma separated minute lists.\n\nA single number string `\"01\"` does not match either condition, so it is silently ignored **forever**.\n\nAlso:\n- The 15min job works correctly now, it will run at 21:15 IST\n- The scheduler was hanging because `memory_batch_sync.py` is broken and hangs forever, that's why the state file was never updated\n- No log messages are written because the process dies before reaching the save_state() line\n\nThat is why you see zero notifications."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"bytedance-seed/dola-seed-2.0-pro:free","usage":{"input":699,"output":194,"cacheRead":34104,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34997,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775921565385,"responseId":"0217759215665764883e653edd60bc78b7b920f959874d915a850"}}
