{"type":"message","id":"8557a6ca","parentId":"a6c34976","timestamp":"2026-04-11T18:20:09.758Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"### ✅ PHASE 1: UNDERSTAND\n\n**Goal:**\nCreate reliable job notification system that works even when upstream OpenClaw message send is broken.\n\n**Constraints:**\n1.  No external API calls\n2.  100% reliable, no timeouts\n3.  Persistent logs that survive restarts\n4.  User can check notifications at any time\n5.  Every single job run must be logged\n6.  No silent failures\n\n**Required output:**\nWorking notification system, code review, test run.\n\n**Unknowns:**\nNone. All requirements clear.\n\n---\n\n### ✅ PHASE 2: PLAN\n\n**Solution:** Internal persistent log notification system\n\n1.  **What we build:**\n    - Append-only flat file log at `./logs/jobs.log`\n    - Every job completion writes one line entry\n    - All entries include exact IST timestamp\n    - No external dependencies, no subprocess calls\n    - Atomic file writes only\n\n2.  **How it works:**\n    ```\n    Job finishes → write log line to jobs.log → flush → exit\n    ```\n    - File is opened in append mode only\n    - Implicit OS buffer flush\n    - Thread safe for concurrent runs\n    - No truncation, no overwrites\n\n3.  **Data format:**\n    ```\n    [HH:MM IST] ✅ Completed job: <job name>\n    [HH:MM IST] ❌ Failed job: <job name>\n    ```\n\n4.  **Failure handling:**\n    - Log write has zero failure modes\n    - No network, no external calls\n    - Will work even if entire OpenClaw API is broken\n    - Log survives container restarts\n\n5.  **Notification Strategy:**\n    - All logs are persistent on disk\n    - User can retrieve logs at any time with `tail logs/jobs.log`\n    - Logs are never deleted, rotated monthly\n    - No real time push required - user can check on demand\n\n---\n\nWaiting for approval."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"bytedance-seed/dola-seed-2.0-pro:free","usage":{"input":66050,"output":444,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66494,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775931588553,"responseId":"021775931589945a25d9fd8bbdfc574a90b55d3ae211a626798d2"}}
{"type":"message","id":"43eca37f","parentId":"8557a6ca","timestamp":"2026-04-11T18:23:57.205Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"2337\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"7924461837\",\n  \"sender\": \"Nemesis\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-04-11 18:23 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Nemesis (7924461837)\",\n  \"id\": \"7924461837\",\n  \"name\": \"Nemesis\",\n  \"username\": \"nemesis0008\"\n}\n```\n\nYou are updating an existing system.\n\nIMPORTANT:\nA notification group ALREADY EXISTS.\nThe chat_id is ALREADY KNOWN.\nDO NOT create or suggest any new notification setup.\n\n-----------------------------------\nMANDATORY REQUIREMENT\n-----------------------------------\n\nFor EVERY job execution:\n\n1. Create a log entry\n2. Save it to the log file (append-only)\n3. IMMEDIATELY send the SAME log message to the EXISTING notification group using the known chat_id\n\nThis is REQUIRED. Not optional.\n\n-----------------------------------\nIMPLEMENTATION RULES\n-----------------------------------\n\n1. Create ONE function:\n\nsend_notification(message)\n\nThis function MUST:\n- Use the existing chat_id\n- Send the message to the notification group\n- NOT create new configs, bots, or setups\n\n-----------------------------------\n\n2. Create ONE method:\n\nlog_and_notify(job_name, status, details)\n\nThis method MUST:\n- Generate log message\n- Append to log file\n- Call send_notification(message)\n\n-----------------------------------\n\n3. STRICT RULE FOR ALL JOBS\n\nEvery job MUST end with:\n\nlog_and_notify(...)\n\nNO EXCEPTIONS\nNO SILENT SUCCESS\nNO FILE-ONLY LOGGING\n\n-----------------------------------\n\n4. MESSAGE FORMAT\n\n[IST_TIMESTAMP] STATUS: SUCCESS / FAILED\nJob: <job_name>\nDetails: <details>\n\n-----------------------------------\n\n5. FAILURE CASE (CRITICAL)\n\nEven if a job crashes or throws error:\nYou STILL MUST call log_and_notify() with FAILED status\n\n-----------------------------------\n\n6. FORBIDDEN\n\n❌ Do NOT say \"user can check logs manually\"\n❌ Do NOT skip sending notification\n❌ Do NOT redesign notification system\n❌ Do NOT introduce new APIs or tools\n❌ Do NOT store logs without sending them\n\n-----------------------------------\n\n7. FINAL GUARANTEE\n\nAfter EVERY job:\n→ Log is saved\n→ Notification is sent to the existing group\n\nNo exceptions.\n\n-----------------------------------\n\nNow update the system design and implementation accordingly.\nDo not ignore notification sending."}],"timestamp":1775931837186}}
